</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>ha-store-name attribute</primary>
</indexterm> <literal>ha-store-name</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>cluster name</para></entry>
<entry>
<para>(optional) Specifies the HADB database name.</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>auto-manage-ha-store attribute</primary>
</indexterm> <literal>auto-manage-ha-store</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>true</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>(optional) If <literal>true</literal>, the life cycle of the highly available
store is matched with the life cycle of the highly available cluster. The store is
started or stopped with the cluster. It is removed when the cluster is deleted. If <literal>
