<entry>
<para>(optional) Specifies the <literal>jndi-name</literal> of the  <olink targetptr="abhcz">
jdbc-resource</olink> used for connections to the HADB for session persistence.</para>
<para>For more information about setting up a connection pool and JDBC resource for
the HADB, see the description of the <literal>configure-ha-cluster</literal> command
in the <citetitle><olink targetdoc="SJSASEEREFMAN" remap="156"><citetitle remap="book">
Sun Java System Application Server Enterprise Edition 9.0 2006Q1 Reference Manual
</citetitle></olink></citetitle>.</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>ha-store-healthcheck-enabled attribute</primary>
</indexterm> <literal>ha-store-<?SolBook preflinebreak>healthcheck-<?SolBook preflinebreak>enabled
</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>false</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>(optional) If <literal>true</literal>, periodic checking is done to detect if
the HADB has become available again after a failure. If the health check succeeds,
persistence to the HADB is resumed.</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>ha-store-healthcheck-interval-in-seconds attribute</primary>
</indexterm> <literal>ha-store-<?SolBook preflinebreak>healthcheck-<?SolBook preflinebreak>interval-<?SolBook preflinebreak>in-seconds
</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>5</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>(optional) Specifies the interval at which the HADB's health is checked. The
checking begins only after a failure is detected.</para></entry>
</row>
</tbody>
