<sect1 id="abhcc"><title>E</title>
<sect2 id="abhcd"><title>ejb-container</title>
<indexterm>
<primary>ejb-container element</primary>
</indexterm>
<para>Configures the EJB container. Stateless session beans are maintained in pools.
Stateful session beans have session affinity and are cached. Entity beans associated
with a database primary key are also cached. Entity beans not yet associated with
a primary key are maintained in pools. Pooled entity beans are used to run  <literal>
ejbCreate()</literal> and finder methods.</para>
<sect3><title>Superelements</title>
<para><olink targetptr="abhbq">config</olink></para></sect3>
<sect3><title>Subelements</title>
<para>The following table describes subelements for the <literal>ejb-container</literal> element.
</para>
<table frame="topbot" pgwide="1"><title><literal>ejb-container</literal>  Subelements
</title>
<tgroup cols="3"><colspec colnum="1" colwidth="142.24*"><colspec colnum="2" colwidth="0.60in">
<colspec colnum="3" colwidth="136.76*">
<thead>
<row>
