</sect1><![ %Enterprise; [<sect1 id="GAFWQ"><title>G</title>
<sect2 id="GAFWX"><title>group-management-service</title>
<indexterm>
<primary>group-management-service element</primary>
</indexterm>
<para>Configures the Group Management Service (GMS), an in-process service that provides
cluster monitoring and group communication services. The GMS performs the following
functions:</para>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Notifies registered modules in an &ProductName; instance when one
or more members in the cluster fail.</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Provides the ability to send and receive messages between a group
of processes.</para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>
<para>The GMS is built atop a configurable stack of protocols. Each protocol has properties
that can be changed for a given network and deployment topology. Protocols in the
GMS are as follows:</para>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>FD protocol enables its members to periodically monitor other group
members to determine their availability in the group.</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Merge protocol reunites subgroups that formed as a result of a network
partition after such a partition has healed.</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Ping protocol is used for discovery of the group and its members.
</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>VS protocol verifies suspect instances by adding a verification layer
to mark a failure suspicion as a confirmed failure.</para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>
<sect3><title>Superelements</title>
<para><olink targetptr="abhbq">config</olink></para></sect3>
<sect3><title>Subelements</title>
