<primary>default virtual server</primary>
<secondary>for an http-listener element</secondary>
</indexterm>default <olink targetptr="abhfg">virtual-server</olink> for this particular
listener.</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>server-name attribute</primary>
</indexterm><literal>server-name</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>none</para></entry>
<entry>
<para>Tells the server what to put in the host name section of any URLs it sends to
the client. This affects URLs the server automatically generates; it doesn&rsquo;t
affect the URLs for directories and files stored in the server. If your server uses
an alias, the <literal>server-name</literal> should be the alias name.</para>
<para>If a colon and port number are appended, that port is used in URLs the server
sends to the client.</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>redirect-port attribute</primary>
</indexterm><literal>redirect-port</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
