<para>The following table describes properties for the <literal>http-listener</literal> element.
Any of these properties can be defined as an <olink targetptr="abhcq">http-service
</olink> property, so that it applies to all <literal>http-listener</literal> elements.
</para>
<table frame="topbot" pgwide="1"><title><literal>http-listener</literal>  Properties
</title>
<tgroup cols="3"><colspec colnum="1" colwidth="55.42*"><colspec colnum="2" colwidth="56.77*">
<colspec colnum="3" colwidth="176.82*">
<thead>
<row>
<entry>
<para>Property</para></entry>
<entry>
<para>Default</para></entry>
<entry>
<para>Description</para></entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>recycle-objects property</primary>
</indexterm><literal>recycle-objects</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>true</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>If <literal>true</literal>, recycles internal objects instead of using the VM
garbage collector.</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>reader-threads property</primary>
</indexterm><literal>reader-threads</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>0</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>Specifies the number of reader threads, which read bytes from the non-blocking
socket.</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>acceptor-queue-length property</primary>
</indexterm><literal>acceptor-queue-<?SolBook preflinebreak>length</literal></para>
</entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>4096</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>Specifies the length of the acceptor thread queue. Once full, connections are
rejected.</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>reader-queue-length property</primary>
</indexterm><literal>reader-queue-<?SolBook preflinebreak>length</literal></para>
</entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>4096</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>Specifies the length of the reader thread queue. Once full, connections are
rejected.</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>use-nio-direct-bytebuffer property</primary>
</indexterm><literal>use-nio-direct-<?SolBook preflinebreak>bytebuffer</literal></para>
</entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>true</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>If <literal>true</literal>, specifies that the NIO direct <literal>ByteBuffer
</literal> is used. In a limited resource environment, it might be faster to use non-direct
Java's <literal>ByteBuffer</literal> by setting a value of <literal>false</literal>.
</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>authPassthroughEnabled property</primary>
</indexterm><literal>authPassthrough<?SolBook preflinebreak>Enabled</literal></para>
</entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>false</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>If <literal>true</literal>, indicates that this <literal>http-listener</literal> element
receives traffic from an SSL-terminating load balancer, which is responsible for forwarding
(using custom HTTP headers) any SSL related information (such as <literal>keysize
</literal> and the authenticated client certificate chain) to this <literal>http-listener
</literal> as if this <literal>http-listener</literal> itself had received the SSL
traffic.</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>proxyHandler property</primary>
</indexterm><literal>proxyHandler</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>com.sun.<?SolBook preflinebreak>enterprise.<?SolBook preflinebreak>web.<?SolBook preflinebreak>ProxyHandlerImpl
</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>Specifies a custom implementation of the <literal>com.sun.appserv.ProxyHandler
</literal> abstract class, which is responsible for processing any SSL related information
(such as <literal>keysize</literal> and the authenticated client certificate chain)
received from an SSL-terminating load balancer. Only used if <literal>authPassthroughEnabled
</literal> is set to <literal>true</literal>. </para>
<para>The default implementation reads the SSL <literal>keysize</literal> from an
HTTP request header named <literal>Proxy-keysize</literal>, and the SSL client certificate
chain from an HTTP request header named <literal>Proxy-auth-cert</literal>. The <literal>
Proxy-auth-cert</literal> value is supposed to contain the BASE-64 encoded client
certificate chain without the <literal>BEGIN CERTIFICATE</literal> and <literal>END
CERTIFICATE</literal> boundaries and with <literal>\n</literal> replaced with <literal>
% d% a</literal>.</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>bufferSize property</primary>
</indexterm><literal>bufferSize</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>4096</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>Specifies the size, in bytes, of the buffer to be provided for input streams
created by HTTP listeners.</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>connectionTimeout property</primary>
</indexterm><literal>connection<?SolBook preflinebreak>Timeout</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>12000</literal> (12 seconds)</para></entry>
<entry>
<para>Specifies the number of milliseconds HTTP listeners wait, after accepting a
connection, for the request URI line to be presented.</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>maxKeepAliveRequests property</primary>
</indexterm><literal>maxKeepAlive<?SolBook preflinebreak>Requests</literal></para>
</entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>1000</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>Specifies the maximum number of HTTP requests that can be pipelined until the
connection is closed by the server. Set this property to <literal>1</literal> to disable
HTTP/1.0 keep-alive, as well as HTTP/1.1 keep-alive and pipelining.</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>traceEnabled property</primary>
</indexterm><literal>traceEnabled</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>true</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>If <literal>true</literal>, enables the TRACE operation. Set this property to <literal>
false</literal> to make the &ProductName; less susceptible to cross-site scripting
attacks.</para></entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</sect3>
