</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>authPassthroughEnabled property</primary>
</indexterm><literal>authPassthrough<?SolBook preflinebreak>Enabled</literal></para>
</entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>false</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>If <literal>true</literal>, indicates that the <olink targetptr="abhco">http-listener
</olink> subelements receive traffic from an SSL-terminating load balancer, which
is responsible for forwarding (using custom HTTP headers) any SSL related information
(such as <literal>keysize</literal> and the authenticated client certificate chain)
to the <literal>http-listener</literal> as if the <literal>http-listener</literal> itself
had received the SSL traffic.</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>proxyHandler property</primary>
</indexterm><literal>proxyHandler</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>com.sun.<?SolBook preflinebreak>enterprise.<?SolBook preflinebreak>web.<?SolBook preflinebreak>ProxyHandlerImpl
</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>Specifies a custom implementation of the <literal>com.sun.appserv.ProxyHandler
</literal> abstract class, which is responsible for processing any SSL related information
(such as <literal>keysize</literal> and the authenticated client certificate chain)
received from an SSL-terminating load balancer. Only used if <literal>authPassthroughEnabled
</literal> is set to <literal>true</literal>. </para>
<para>The default implementation reads the SSL <literal>keysize</literal> from an
HTTP request header named <literal>Proxy-keysize</literal>, and the SSL client certificate
chain from an HTTP request header named <literal>Proxy-auth-cert</literal>. The <literal>
Proxy-auth-cert</literal> value is supposed to contain the BASE-64 encoded client
certificate chain without the <literal>BEGIN CERTIFICATE</literal> and <literal>END
CERTIFICATE</literal> boundaries and with <literal>\n</literal> replaced with <literal>
% d% a</literal>.</para></entry>
