<sect2 id="abhdl"><title>log-service</title>
<indexterm>
<primary>log-service element</primary>
</indexterm><indexterm>
<primary>logging settings in domain.xml</primary>
</indexterm><indexterm>
<primary>server log file</primary>
</indexterm>
<para>Configures the <emphasis>server log</emphasis> file, which stores messages from
the default virtual server. Messages from other configured virtual servers also go
here, unless the <literal>log-file</literal>  attribute is explicitly specified in
the <literal>virtual-server</literal> element. The default name is <literal>server.log
</literal>.</para>
<para>Other log files are configured by other elements:</para>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>A <indexterm>
<primary>virtual servers</primary>
<secondary>log file for</secondary>
</indexterm> <emphasis>virtual server log</emphasis> file stores messages from a <literal>
virtual-server</literal>  element that has an explicitly specified <literal>log-file
</literal> attribute. See <olink targetptr="abhfg">virtual-server</olink>.</para>
</listitem><![ %Enterprise; [<listitem><para>The <indexterm>
<primary>access log file</primary>
</indexterm><emphasis>access log</emphasis> file stores HTTP access messages from
the default virtual server. The default name is <literal>access.log</literal>. See <olink
targetptr="abhaz">access-log</olink> and <olink targetptr="abhcm">http-access-log
</olink>.</para></listitem>]]>
<listitem><para>The <indexterm>
<primary>transaction log file</primary>
</indexterm><emphasis>transaction log</emphasis> files store transaction messages
from the default virtual server. The default name of the directory for these files
is <literal>tx</literal>. See <olink targetptr="abhfc">transaction-service</olink>.
</para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>
<sect3><title>Superelements</title>
