<para>Specifies a property. A property adds configuration information to its parent
element that is one or both of the following:</para>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Optional with respect to the &ProductName;</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Needed by a system or object that the &ProductName; doesn&rsquo;t
have knowledge of, such as an LDAP server or a Java class</para><para>For example,
an <literal>auth-realm</literal> element can include <literal>property</literal> 
subelements:</para>
<programlisting>&lt;auth-realm name="file"
     classname="com.sun.enterprise.security.auth.realm.file.FileRealm">
     &lt;property name="file" value="&DomainDir;/config/keyfile"/>
     &lt;property name="jaas-context" value="fileRealm"/>
 &lt;/auth-realm></programlisting>
<para>Which properties an <literal>auth-realm</literal> element uses depends on the
value of the <literal>auth-realm</literal> element&rsquo;s <literal>name</literal> attribute.
The <literal>file</literal> realm uses <literal>file</literal> and <literal>jaas-context
</literal>  properties. Other realms use different properties.</para></listitem>
