<primary>properties</primary>
<secondary>system</secondary>
</indexterm>
<para>Specifies a system property. A system property defines a common value for a
setting at one of these levels, from highest to lowest: <olink targetptr="abhcb">
domain</olink>, <![ %Enterprise; [<olink targetptr="abhbn">cluster</olink>, ]]><olink
targetptr="abhep">server</olink>, or <olink targetptr="abhbq">config</olink>. A value
set at a higher level can be overridden at a lower level. Some system properties are
predefined; see <olink targetptr="abhey">system-property</olink>. You can also create
system properties using this element.</para>
<para>The following example shows the use of a predefined system property:</para>
<programlisting>&lt;log-service file="${com.sun.aas.instanceRoot}/logs/server.log">
    &lt;module-log-levels admin=INFO .../>
&lt;/log-service></programlisting>
<para>The following example shows the creation and use of a system property:</para>
<programlisting>&lt;config name="config1">
    ...
    &lt;http-service>
        ...
        &lt;http-listener id="ls1" host="0.0.0.0" port="${ls1-port}"/>
        ...
    &lt;/http-service>
    ...
    &lt;system-property name="ls1-port" value="8080"/>
&lt;/config></programlisting>
<sect3><title>Superelements</title>
<para><![ %Enterprise; [<olink targetptr="abhbn">cluster</olink>, ]]><olink targetptr="abhbq">
config</olink>, <olink targetptr="abhcb">domain</olink>, <olink targetptr="abhep">
server</olink></para></sect3>
