<row rowsep="1">
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>automatic-recovery attribute</primary>
</indexterm> <literal>automatic-<?SolBook preflinebreak>recovery</literal></para>
</entry>
<entry><![ %Platform; [<para><literal>false</literal></para>]]><![ %Enterprise; [<para><literal>
true</literal></para>]]></entry>
<entry>
<para>(optional) If <literal>true</literal>, the server instance attempts transaction
recovery during startup.</para>
<para><remark role="reviewer">Default is &ldquo;false&rdquo; for Platform Edition.
</remark></para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>timeout-in-seconds attribute</primary>
</indexterm> <literal>timeout-in-<?SolBook preflinebreak>seconds</literal></para>
</entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>0</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>(optional) Specifies the amount of time after which the transaction is aborted.
If set to <literal>0</literal>, the transaction never times out.</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>tx-log-dir attribute</primary>
</indexterm><literal>tx-log-dir</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>directory specified by the <literal>log-root</literal> attribute of the <olink
targetptr="abhcb">domain</olink> element</para></entry>
<entry>
<para>(optional) Specifies the parent directory of the <indexterm>
<primary>transaction log file</primary>
</indexterm>transaction log directory <replaceable>instance-name</replaceable><literal>
/tx</literal>. The directory in which the transaction logs are kept must be writable
by the user account under which the server runs. A relative path is relative to the <literal>
log-root</literal>  attribute of the <olink targetptr="abhcb">domain</olink> element.
</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>heuristic-decision attribute</primary>
</indexterm> <literal>heuristic-<?SolBook preflinebreak>decision</literal></para>
</entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>rollback</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>(optional) If the outcome of a distributed transaction cannot be determined
because other participants are unreachable, this property determines the outcome.
Allowed values are <literal>rollback</literal> and <literal>commit</literal>.</para>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>retry-timeout-in-seconds attribute</primary>
</indexterm> <literal>retry-timeout-<?SolBook preflinebreak>in-seconds</literal></para>
</entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>600</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>(optional) Determines the retry time in the following scenarios:</para>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>At the transaction recovery time, if resources are unreachable.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem><para>If there are any transient exceptions in the second phase of a two
phase commit protocol.</para><para>A negative value specifies infinite retries. A
value of <literal>0</literal> (zero) specifies no retries. A positive value indicates
the time after which a retry is attempted.</para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>keypoint-interval attribute</primary>
</indexterm> <literal>keypoint-<?SolBook preflinebreak>interval</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>2048</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>(optional) Specifies the number of transactions between keypoint operations
in the log. Keypoint operations reduce the size of the transaction log file by compressing
it. A larger value for this attribute (for example, <literal>4096</literal>) results
in a larger transaction log file, but fewer keypoint operations and potentially better
performance. A smaller value (for example, <literal>100</literal>) results in smaller
log files, but slightly reduced performance due to the greater frequency of keypoint
operations.</para></entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
