<colspec colnum="3" colwidth="201.79*">
<thead>
<row>
<entry>
<para>Attribute</para></entry>
<entry>
<para>Default</para></entry>
<entry>
<para>Description</para></entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row rowsep="1">
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>id attribute</primary>
<secondary>virtual-server element</secondary>
</indexterm><literal>id</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>none</para></entry>
<entry>
<para>Virtual server ID. This is a unique ID that allows lookup of a specific virtual
server. A virtual server ID cannot begin with a number.</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>http-listeners attribute</primary>
</indexterm> <literal>http-<?SolBook preflinebreak>listeners</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>none</para></entry>
<entry>
<para>(optional) In a comma-separated list, references <literal>id</literal> attributes
of <olink targetptr="abhco">http-listener</olink> elements that specify the connection(s)
the virtual server uses. Required only for a <literal>virtual-server</literal> that
is not referenced by the <literal>default-<?SolBook preflinebreak>virtual-<?SolBook preflinebreak>server
</literal> attribute of an  <literal>http-listener</literal>.</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>default-web-module attribute</primary>
</indexterm> <literal>default-<?SolBook preflinebreak>web-<?SolBook preflinebreak>module
</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>system default web module</para></entry>
<entry>
<para>(optional) References the <literal>name</literal> attribute of the <indexterm>
<primary>web module</primary>
<secondary>default</secondary>
</indexterm>default  <olink targetptr="abhfk">web-module</olink> for this virtual
server, which responds to requests that cannot be resolved to other web modules deployed
to this virtual server (see the  <olink targetptr="abhbf">application-ref</olink> element).
</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>hosts attribute</primary>
</indexterm><literal>hosts</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>none</para></entry>
<entry>
<para>A comma-separated list of values, each of which selects the current virtual
server when included in the <literal>Host</literal> request header. Two or more  <literal>
virtual-server</literal> elements that reference or are referenced by the same  <literal>
http-listener</literal> cannot have any <literal>hosts</literal> values in common.
</para></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>state attribute</primary>
</indexterm><literal>state</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>on</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>(optional) Determines whether a <literal>virtual-server</literal> is active
(<literal>on</literal>) or inactive (<literal>off</literal>, <literal>disabled</literal>).
The default is <literal>on</literal> (active). When inactive, a <literal>virtual-server
</literal>  does not service requests. If a <literal>virtual-server</literal> is <literal>
disabled</literal>, only the global server administrator can turn it <literal>on</literal>.
</para></entry>
</row><![ %Enterprise; [<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>docroot attribute</primary>
</indexterm><literal>docroot</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para>none</para></entry>
<entry>
<para>(optional) Specifies the document root for this virtual server.</para></entry>
</row>]]>
<row>
<entry>
<para><indexterm>
<primary>log-file attribute</primary>
</indexterm><literal>log-file</literal></para></entry>
<entry>
<para><literal>server.log</literal> in the directory specified by the <literal>log-root
</literal>  attribute of the <olink targetptr="abhcb">domain</olink> element</para>
</entry>
<entry>
<para>(optional) Writes this virtual server&rsquo;s log messages to a log file separate
from the server log. The file and directory in which the virtual server log is kept
must be writable by the user account under which the server runs. See the  <olink
targetptr="abhdl">log-service</olink> description for details about logs.</para></entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
